A RESOLUTION
To commend Acadiana Legislative Delegation student worker Ty Hebert on the occasion of
his graduation from Louisiana State University.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Ty Hebert for his service to the Acadiana
Legislative Delegation and to commend him on the occasion of his graduation from
Louisiana State University; and
WHEREAS, Ty is graduating with a bachelor of science degree in agricultural
business from Louisiana State University on May 15, 2026; and
WHEREAS, Ty is a member of Kappa Sigma and served as fraternity president from
November 2024 to November 2025; he was nominated for Interfraternity Conference
President of the Year for his service; and
WHEREAS, Ty led a fundraiser that raised over fifty thousand dollars for the
military heroes campaign that benefits wounded United States Navy SEALs; he also hosted
a leadership development workshop to benefit youth in agriculture; and
WHEREAS, Ty is a native of Cow Island, Louisiana, and served as president of the
American Junior Brahman Association during his freshman year; and
WHEREAS, Ty has displayed an outstanding work ethic, attention to detail, and
willingness to take on a wide range of responsibilities during his time with the Acadiana
Legislative Delegation, which began on November 26, 2023; and
WHEREAS, Ty has supported community engagement efforts, including assisting
with a successful crawfish boil, and contributed to the review and development of detailed
legislation; he has also made a concerted effort to build and maintain positive working
relationships within the delegation office and fostered a collaborative and supportive
environment; and
